<center> 
 <h1> 
       Petri-Net
 </h1>
</center> 
<H3>

 As a tool&nbsp;for Software System Modeling, Petri-Net 
has
 
 
 </H3>
<UL>
  <LI>
  <H3>Advantage:</H3></LI></UL>
<OL dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
  <OL>
    <LI>
    <H3>Allowing the modeling of concurrency, sychronization and resource 
    sharing behavior of a system.</H3>
    <LI>
    <H3>There are many theoretical results associated with Petri-Nets for 
    analysis of such issues detection and performance analysis. Example: 
    DesignCPN tools to simulate Petri-Net.</H3></LI></OL></OL>
<UL>
  <LI>
  <H3>Disadvantage:</H3></LI></UL>
<OL>
  <OL>
    <LI>
    <H3>It's not easy for developers to&nbsp;draw a Petri-Net, especially for 
    complex systems.&nbsp;</H3>
    <LI>
    <H3>Having difficulty to&nbsp;model objects and 
    relation between objects.</H3></LI></OL></OL></BODY>
